 ## Issue
 
-The Overview step could mark a coversheet row as `F&R Needed = Yes` while writing `0` to the Overview F&R item count column.
+The Overview step had two related problems across the `v00.04.010` / `v00.04.011` fixes:
 
-The immediate cause was that the script used different status sets for the two fields:
+1. The script needed to evaluate F&R status from the correct CLIN row scope.
+   - If one or more CLIN rows are marked `OpDiv Approval = Yes`, use those approved rows.
+   - If no CLIN rows are marked with OpDiv approval, fall back to all listed CLIN rows.
 
-- `F&R Needed` was triggered by `Pending`, `N/A`, or `NA`.
-- The numeric F&R count only counted `Pending` or `Approved`.
+2. The numeric F&R count was briefly expanded too far in `v00.04.011`.
+   - `N/A` / `NA` can mean the PR still needs F&R attention.
+   - But `N/A` / `NA` should not be counted as an F&R item.
 
-That meant an `N/A` row could cause `F&R Needed = Yes` but still not be included in the count.
+## Corrected rule in v00.04.012
 
-## Fix in v00.04.011
+`02_overview_file_script.py` now applies these rules:
 
-`02_overview_file_script.py` now uses the same CLIN-row scope for both fields:
+### Row scope
 
-- If one or more CLIN rows are marked `OpDiv Approval = Yes`, the Overview F&R logic uses those approved rows.
-- If no CLIN rows are marked with OpDiv approval, the Overview F&R logic falls back to all listed CLIN rows.
+- If any rows are marked `OpDiv Approval = Yes`, both the `F&R Needed` flag and numeric F&R count evaluate those approved rows only.
+- If no rows are marked `OpDiv Approval = Yes`, both values evaluate all listed CLIN rows.
 
-The F&R item count now includes these statuses:
+### F&R Needed flag
+
+The Overview writes `F&R Needed = Yes` when an in-scope row has one of these F&R statuses:
 
 - `Pending`
-- `Approved`
-- `N/A`
-- `NA`
-- common N/A variants such as `N.A.` and `Not Applicable`
+- `N/A` / `NA` / common N/A variants
+
+`Approved` alone does not make `F&R Needed = Yes`, because it is already approved.
 
-The `F&R Needed` flag still uses the original trigger statuses:
+### Numeric F&R item count
+
+The numeric F&R count includes only these statuses:
 
 - `Pending`
-- `N/A` / `NA`
+- `Approved`
 
-So approved-only F&R rows may be counted as F&R items, but they do not by themselves make `F&R Needed = Yes` because the F&R is already approved.
+`N/A` / `NA` does not increment the F&R count.
 
 ## Validation
 
 Targeted in-memory workbook tests confirmed:
 
-1. A coversheet with no OpDiv approval rows and an `N/A` F&R status now produces `F&R Needed = Yes` and an F&R count of `1`.
-2. A coversheet with approved rows uses only the approved rows for both the F&R yes/no flag and the F&R count.
-3. A pending status on a non-approved row does not trigger F&R when approved rows exist elsewhere in the same CLIN table.
+1. A coversheet with no OpDiv approval rows and one `N/A` F&R status produces `F&R Needed = Yes` and F&R count `0`.
+2. A coversheet with no OpDiv approval rows and statuses `Pending`, `N/A`, and `Approved` produces `F&R Needed = Yes` and F&R count `2`.
+3. A coversheet with only `Approved` produces `F&R Needed = No` and F&R count `1`.
+4. When approved rows exist, non-approved rows are excluded from both the flag and the count.
